      "parameters": {
        "inputText": "=Subject:  {{ $json.Subject }}\nEmail body:{{ $json.snippet }}",
        "categories": {
          "categories": [
            {
              "category": "Promotional / Sales",
              "description": "Marketing and promotional emails intended to advertise products, services, discounts, special offers, newsletters, product launches, coupons, seasonal sales, or brand announcements. These emails are commercial in nature and encourage purchases or user engagement with a business."
            },
            {
              "category": "Personal",
              "description": "Emails related to personal communication between individuals, including messages from family, friends, classmates, colleagues, or acquaintances. These emails typically involve conversations, greetings, invitations, personal updates, or non-commercial discussions and do not promote products, services, or financial transactions."
            },
            {
              "category": "Internship & Jobs",
              "description": "Evaluate the following factors:\n- The sender appears to be a legitimate recruiter or organization.\n- The company or organization is clearly identified.\n- The internship details are specific and professionally written.\n- The email contains a clear hiring process or interview invitation.\n- The role matches a typical internship or entry-level opportunity.\n- The email requests reasonable information only.\n- There are no signs of phishing, scams, unrealistic promises, or suspicious links.\n- The opportunity appears credible and worth pursuing.\n\nReturn your response ONLY as valid JSON in the following format:\n\n{\n  \"classification\": \"High Priority Internship\" | \"Normal Internship\" | \"Not an Internship\",\n  \"confidence\": 0-100,\n  \"priority\": \"High\" | \"Medium\" | \"Low\",\n  \"reason\": \"Brief explanation for your decision.\"\n}\n\nConfidence Guidelines:\n- 90–100: Verified-looking opportunity with interview invitation, assessment, recruiter contact, or official company communication.\n- 70–89: Appears to be a genuine internship opportunity with strong indicators of legitimacy.\n- 50–69: Internship-related but lacks sufficient details or credibility.\n- Below 50: Not an internship or appears suspicious.\n\nOnly classify an email as \"High Priority Internship\" if the confidence score is 70 or higher."
            },
            {
              "category": "Payments & Finance",
              "description": "Emails related to financial activities, including payment confirmations, invoices, receipts, subscription renewals, billing statements, bank notifications, credit card alerts, salary notifications, refunds, tax documents, and transaction confirmations. Any email whose primary purpose is to communicate financial information belongs here."
            },
            {
              "category": "Misleading / Scam",
              "description": "Classify an email as \"Misleading\" if it contains one or more of the following:\n- Phishing attempts\n- Fake internship or job offers\n- Fake bank or payment notifications\n- Requests for passwords, OTPs, or sensitive information\n- Suspicious links or attachments\n- Impersonation of a trusted person, company, or organization\n- Unrealistic rewards, lotteries, giveaways, or prizes\n- Urgent threats designed to pressure the recipient\n- Requests to transfer money or gift cards\n- Poor grammar or suspicious sender identity combined with other red flags\n\nIf the email appears legitimate, classify it as \"Legitimate\".\n\nAnalyze the sender, subject, and email body carefully before making a decision.\n\nReturn your response ONLY as valid JSON in the following format:\n\n{\n  \"classification\": \"Misleading\" | \"Legitimate\",\n  \"confidence\": 0-100,\n  \"reason\": \"A concise explanation of why the email was classified this way.\"\n}\n\nConfidence Guidelines:\n- 95–100: Almost certainly misleading or phishing.\n- 80–94: Strong evidence of misleading or fraudulent intent.\n- 60–79: Some suspicious indicators, but uncertain.\n- Below 60: Appears legitimate.\n\nOnly classify an email as \"Misleading\" if your confidence is 80 or higher."
            },
            {
              "category": "Updates & Notifications",
              "description": "Informational emails that notify users about account activity, security alerts, password resets, order status, shipping updates, delivery confirmations, system notifications, service announcements, or changes to an account or application. These emails provide important updates but are not promotional or personal conversations."
            }
          ]
        },
        "options": {}
      },
